title: Big Tech hearing on Capitol Hill set for Monday officially postponed

title: Apple, Amazon, Facebook and Google CEO congressional hearing officially delayed
text: The highly anticipated antitrust hearing featuring CEOs from Amazon, Apple, Facebook and Google has been officially postponed.

title: Tech stocks lose steam. What to make of the moves
text: Big Tech dragged on the broader market on Friday, and market analysts are split on what could be in store for the soaring sector.

title: Antitrust hearing with CEOs of Amazon, Apple, Facebook, Google will likely be delayed
text: A hotly anticipated House antitrust hearing with the CEOs of Amazon, Apple, Facebook, and Google set for Monday will likely be delayed according to reports from CNBC, The Verge, and Axios.

title: Facebook Gives You Something Extra, Says Dinakar Singh
text: Dinakar Singh, founder and co-chief executive officer of Axon Capital, explains why he's invested in Alphabet and Facebook, but not Amazon in a discussion about tech stocks. He spoke exclusively to Erik Schatzker on "Bloomberg Front Row."

title: Should We Maintain High Expectations For FAANG?
text: As COVID-19 continues to hinder the economy and business throughout the country, stock market sentiment has told a very different story and showed that there is a huge disconnect right now between the economy and the markets.

title: Facebook (FB) to Report Q2 Earnings: What's in the Cards?
text: Facebook's (FB) Q2 results are likely to reflect continued user growth. However, ad sales are expected to have been drained by the coronavirus pandemic.

title: Turkish MPs to vote on bill that could block Facebook and Twitter
text: Law would give authorities power to regulate content on large social media sites

title: Bezos, Zuck and tech CEOs vs. Congress: Explained
text: The CEOs of Apple, Amazon, Facebook and Google have been called to Washington to answer tough questions about just how much power their companies wield.

title: Big tech antitrust probe report from Congress likely by early fall
text: A much-anticipated deep dive into antitrust allegations against four of America's largest tech companies and recommendations on how to tame their market power could be released by late summer or early fall from the House of Representatives Judiciary Committee's antitrust panel, senior committee aides said.
